AgriAid – Potential Challenges & Overcoming Strategies
 
<b>Potential Challenges</b>
<b>Overcoming Strategies</b>
■ Limited Internet Connectivity in Rural Areas
■ Use lightweight mobile app, offline caching, and SMS/IVR-based updates for farmers with weak networks.
■ Data Accuracy & Reliability (Weather, Market Prices)
■ Integrate with trusted APIs (IMD, govt. mandi portals), apply cross-verification and AI-based data cleaning.
■ Language & Literacy Barriers
■ Deploy Hindi/Regional voice chatbot, simple icon-based UI, and multilingual support.
■ Farmers’ Digital Adoption
■ Conduct training workshops, provide step-by-step tutorials, and build a farmer community support system.
■ Scalability with Growing Users
■ Host on cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure), implement modular microservices for flexibility.
■ Data Privacy & Security
■ Ensure data encryption (SSL), role-based access, and comply with government data policies.
